  <title translate="true">XS1690</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword translate="true">XS1690</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">XS1690</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Accessing a member on &apos;member&apos; may cause a runtime exception because it is a field of a marshal-by-reference class</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">This warning occurs when you try to call a method, property, or indexer on a member of a class that derives from MarshalByRefObject, and the member is a value type. Objects that inherit from MarshalByRefObject are typically intended to be marshaled by reference across an application domain. If any code ever attempts to directly access the value-type member of such an object across an application domain, a runtime exception will occur. To resolve the warning, first copy the member into a local variable and call the method on that variable.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The following sample generates XS1690:</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Code with box"><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">// XS1690.prg  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">using System;  </text><br/><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">class WarningXS1690: MarshalByRefObject  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">{  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">   int i = 5;  </text><br/><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">   public static void Main()   </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">   {  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">     WarningXS1690 e = new WarningXS1690();  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">     e.i.ToString();   // XS1690  </text><br/><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">     // OK  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">     int i = e.i;  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">     i.ToString();  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">     e.i = i;  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">   }  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">}  </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
  </body>
